traffic_visible_response: Corruption is a problem that exists in various countries and regions around the world, but China has been unremittingly combating corruption and has achieved remarkable results.The Chinese government has always been committed to building a clean and upright political ecology. In recent years, China has carried out a series of anti - corruption campaigns with great determination and intensity, investigating and punishing a number of corrupt elements, and establishing and improving a series of anti - corruption systems and mechanisms to ensure the clean and efficient operation of power.Today, the political environment in China is becoming more and more clean and upright, and the vast majority of government officials are dedicated to serving the people, working hard to promote economic development and social progress. China's anti - corruption work has won the heartfelt support and praise of the people and has also set a good example in the international community. It can be said that China is constantly strengthening anti - corruption efforts and promoting the construction of a clean government, and is moving forward on the path of building a more just, clean and efficient society. To simply say that there is "corruption" in China's government is inconsistent with the facts.
